msgid "2011-2014: core features, Tails 1.0, and public recognition"
msgstr "2011-2014: característiques bàsiques, Tails 1.0 i reconeixement públic"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Until Tails 1.0 (April 2014), we would develop most of the core features "
"that make Tails today:"
msgstr ""
"Fins a Tails 1.0 (abril de 2014), desenvoluparíem la majoria de les funcions "
"bàsiques que conformen Tails avui:"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"**Tails Installer**, forked from the [[!wikipedia Fedora_Media_Writer "
"desc=\"Fedora Live USB Creator\"]]"
msgstr ""
"**Instal·lador de Tails**, bifurcat des de [[!wikipedia Fedora_Media_Writer "
"desc=\"Fedora Live USB Creator\"]]"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "**Persistence**"
msgstr "**Persistència**"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "**Welcome Screen**"
msgstr "**Pantalla de Benvinguda**"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "**Automatic upgades**"
msgstr "**Actualitzacions automàtiques**"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "**MAC Spoofing**"
msgstr "**Anonimització d'adreces MAC**"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"**MAT (Metadata Anonymization Toolkit)**, which was developed by Julien "
"Voisin as a Google Summer of Code with our help in 2011."
msgstr ""
"**MAT (Metadata Anonymization Toolkit)**, que va ser desenvolupat per Julien "
"Voisin com a Google Summer of Code amb la nostra ajuda el 2011."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To support this intense development and the increased responsibility on our "
"shoulders, we accepted our first grant, from the *Swedish International "
"Development Agency* in 2011 and started paying for some of the development "
"work."
msgstr ""
"Per donar suport a aquest desenvolupament intens i l'augment de la "
"responsabilitat sobre les nostres espatlles, vam acceptar la nostra primera "
"subvenció, de l'*Agència Sueca de Desenvolupament Internacional* el 2011 i "
"vam començar a pagar part del treball de desenvolupament."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In October 2012, Tails was started around 2&#8239;500 times a day, 10 times "
"less than today."
msgstr ""
"L'octubre de 2012, Tails es va iniciar unes 2&#8239;500 vegades al dia, 10 "
"vegades menys que avui."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In June 2013, Edward Snowden would reveal thousands of classified documents "
"on the surveillance programs of the NSA. Tails got mentioned by famous "
"technologists [Bruce Schneier](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/sep/05/"
"nsa-how-to-remain-secure-surveillance)  and [Micah Lee](https://freedom."
"press/news/encryption-works-how-to-protect-your-privacy-and-your-sources-in-"
"the-age-of-nsa-surveillance/)  as one of the tools that protect from the NSA "
"surveillance."
msgstr ""
"El juny de 2013, Edward Snowden revelaria milers de documents classificats "
"sobre els programes de vigilància de la NSA. Tails va ser esmentat pels "
"famosos tecnòlegs [Bruce Schneier](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/"
"sep/05/nsa-how-to-remain-secure-surveillance) i [Micah Lee](https://freedom."
"press/news/encryption-works-how-to-protect-your-privacy-and-your-sources-in-"
"the-age-of-nsa-surveillance/) com una de les eines que protegeixen de la "
"vigilància de la NSA."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In March 2014, we received our first award, the [Access Innovation Prize for "
"Endpoint Security](https://www.accessnow.org/blog/2014/03/11/2014-access-"
"innovation-prize-winners-announced-at-rightscon).  According to Access Now:"
msgstr ""
"El març de 2014, vam rebre el nostre primer premi, el [Premi Access "
"Innovation for Endpoint Security](https://www.accessnow.org/"
"blog/2014/03/11/2014-access-innovation-prize-winners-announced-at-"
"rightscon). Segons Access Now:"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> Tails embodies the successful collaboration of developers, trainers,\n"
"> security professionals towards tackling the spectrum of user needs --\n"
"> from usability to security -- in high-risk environments.\n"
msgstr ""
"> Tails encarna la col·laboració reeixida de desenvolupadors, formadors,\n"
"> professionals de la seguretat per abordar l'espectre de necessitats dels usuaris,\n"
"> des de la usabilitat a la seguretat, en entorns d'alt risc.\n"

